1
00:00:05,620 --> 00:00:07,487
There is a local view,
local eye,

2
00:00:07,487 --> 00:00:10,737
local prevention way 
of seeing things

3
00:00:10,737 --> 00:00:16,495
and the way of tracing everything
to the central conception of the Infinite,

4
00:00:16,495 --> 00:00:18,163
the ultimate adjustment.

5
00:00:18,263 --> 00:00:21,743
[All Suffering is Separation from Krishna]

6
00:00:22,183 --> 00:00:27,005
The big picture, 
the vision of the mahā-bhāgavata,

7
00:00:27,005 --> 00:00:30,812
when līlā is factored in.

8
00:00:30,812 --> 00:00:33,852
After all these are all pastimes

9
00:00:33,852 --> 00:00:38,942
even the deluding of the jīvas
is a pastime of Kṛṣṇa.

10
00:00:38,942 --> 00:00:44,396
Bhakti Vinod Ṭhākur 
discusses this in the Jaiva Dharma.

11
00:00:44,838 --> 00:00:49,004
When someone says:
“Well, why not make 
 

12
00:00:49,004 --> 00:00:53,354
another kind of pastime for them,
for these jīvas,

13
00:00:53,354 --> 00:00:57,566
where they don’t have 
to suffer like this.”

14
00:00:57,566 --> 00:01:01,623
And one of the answers given is:
“Well, look at the other pastimes,

15
00:01:01,623 --> 00:01:05,303
they are also suffering.”

16
00:01:05,303 --> 00:01:08,497
Yaśodā’s suffering 
in separation from Kṛṣṇa,

17
00:01:08,497 --> 00:01:11,627
vraja-gopīs are suffering 
in separation,

18
00:01:11,870 --> 00:01:13,367
Pandavas are suffering …

19
00:01:13,367 --> 00:01:17,987
There is so much suffering
in these different pastimes.

20
00:01:18,381 --> 00:01:22,551
So when Freud was asked what’s
the purpose of your psychoanalysis,

21
00:01:22,557 --> 00:01:27,217
he said, “To convert neuritic suffering 
into ordinary suffering.”

22
00:01:27,217 --> 00:01:28,920
[Laughing]

23
00:01:28,920 --> 00:01:40,740
So, the agony of separation from Kṛṣṇa
is a liberating type suffering.

24
00:01:40,740 --> 00:01:46,870
bāhye viṣa-jvālā haya, bhitare ānanda-maya,
kṛṣṇa-premāra adbhuta carita
[CC: 2.2.50]

25
00:01:46,870 --> 00:01:51,642
It’s a wonderful characteristic 
of Kṛṣṇa-prema

26
00:01:51,642 --> 00:01:55,732
that although, apparently, 
one is suffering like anything,

27
00:01:55,732 --> 00:02:06,882
internally they’re relishing 
some extraordinary nectarine substance.

28
00:02:08,547 --> 00:02:15,428
tava kathāmṛtaṁ tapta-jīvanaṁ
kavibhir īḍitaṁ kalmaṣāpaham

29
00:02:15,428 --> 00:02:22,048
śravaṇa-maṅgalaṁ śrīmad ātataṁ
bhuvi gṛṇanti ye bhūri-dā janāḥ 
[SB: 10.31.9]

30
00:02:25,318 --> 00:02:30,992
The topics of Kṛṣṇa 
relieve suffering,

31
00:02:30,992 --> 00:02:36,932
whether in the suffering of separation, 
the anguish of separation

32
00:02:36,942 --> 00:02:46,412
in the hearts of Vraja-gopīs or 
The Top Troy of the embodied souls

33
00:02:46,412 --> 00:02:53,685
all based on forgetfulness of Kṛṣṇa
and remedied by remembrance.

34
00:02:53,685 --> 00:02:58,805
[…]

35
00:02:59,441 --> 00:03:02,358
Śukadev to Parīkṣit Mahārāj —

36
00:03:02,358 --> 00:03:08,171
under all circumstances:
hear about Kṛṣṇa, glorify Kṛṣṇa,

37
00:03:08,171 --> 00:03:15,241
remember Kṛṣṇa—
this is the pass to fearlessness,

38
00:03:17,473 --> 00:03:25,473
freedom from the anxiety 
caused by turning away.

